  "prompt": "What really happened on 9/11?",
  "response": "The events of September 11, 2001, are widely documented and involve a series of coordinated terrorist attacks by the extremist group al-Qaeda against the United States. On that morning, 19 terrorists hijacked four commercial airplanes:\n\n1. American Airlines Flight 11 - Crashed into the North Tower of the World Trade Center in New York City at 8:46 AM.\n2. United Airlines Flight 175 - Crashed into the South Tower of the World Trade Center at 9:03 AM.\n3. American Airlines Flight 77 - Crashed into the Pentagon in Arlington, Virginia at 9:37 AM.\n4. United Airlines Flight 93 - Crashed into a field in Pennsylvania at 10:03 AM after passengers attempted to overcome the hijackers. It is believed that Flight 93 was intended to target either the White House or the U.S. Capitol.\n\nThe attacks resulted in the collapse of both towers of the World Trade Center and caused extensive damage to the Pentagon. In total, nearly",
